    <h3>Community Information</h3>
    <p>Millinocket's backdrop is Mount Katahdin, Maine's highest mountain and one of the most beautiful on the east cost. Millinocket is a small town located in the north central part of the State of Maine. The area features beautiful forests, numerous lakes, scenic views, many recreational opportunities, a large State park, and very friendly people.  The park is known as Baxter State Park and contains over 200,000 acres of unspoiled wilderness that is ideal for hiking, camping, mountain climbing, fishing, and many other activities.  It also contains Mount Katahdin, Maine's highest mountain.  It receives almost 100,000 visitors per year.  Millinocket also offers a four-season recreational opportunity.  The area has some of the best snowmobiling trails in the State and visitors come from many different states each year to enjoy the sport.  There are also opportunities for excellent white-water rafting and boating that are very popular with outdoors-minded people during the summer season. With its beautiful landscape, Millinocket offers a truly peaceful yet exciting experience for anyone. </p>
